## 11. Security Considerations

> [!CAUTION]
> The following vulnerabilities are **OPEN** and must be fixed before production traffic.

### 11.1 Critical — Fix Immediately

#### ISSUE-001: SQL Injection in Returns Filter
```php
// ❌ CURRENT (api/admin.php ~line 341)
$where = $filter !== 'all' ? "WHERE r.admin_status = '$filter'" : '';

// ✅ FIX
$allowed = ['pending', 'approved', 'declined'];
$where = in_array($filter, $allowed) ? "WHERE r.admin_status = ?" : '';
// Use prepared statement with $where condition
```

#### ISSUE-002: No OTP Rate Limiting
```php
// ✅ FIX — Add to api/auth.php before sending OTP
$stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT COUNT(*) FROM otp_attempts 
    WHERE phone = ? AND created_at > DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 10 MINUTE)");
$stmt->execute([$phone]);
if ((int)$stmt->fetchColumn() >= 5) {
    respond(false, 'Too many OTP requests. Please wait 10 minutes.');
}
$pdo->prepare("INSERT INTO otp_attempts (phone) VALUES (?)")->execute([$phone]);
```

#### ISSUE-003: No Session Regeneration After Login
```php
// ✅ Add immediately after setting $_SESSION['user_id']
session_regenerate_id(true);
```

#### ISSUE-004: Blocked Users Can Re-Login
```php
// ✅ Add to login handler after fetching user row
if ($user['is_blocked']) {
    respond(false, 'Your account has been blocked. Contact support.');
}
```

### 11.2 High Priority — Fix This Week

#### ISSUE-005: Missing Security Headers
```php
// ✅ Add to config.php
header('X-Frame-Options: DENY');
header('X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff');
header('X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block');
header('Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin');
header("Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://checkout.razorpay.com https://www.gstatic.com;");
```

#### ISSUE-006: cron.php Publicly Accessible
```php
// ✅ Add to top of cron.php
if (!isset($_GET['token']) || $_GET['token'] !== getenv('CRON_SECRET')) {
    http_response_code(403); die('Forbidden');
}
```

### 11.3 Medium Priority — Before Scale

#### ISSUE-007: Coupon Race Condition
```php
// ✅ Use transaction + row lock
$pdo->beginTransaction();
$stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT * FROM coupons WHERE id = ? FOR UPDATE");
// ... perform usage check and insert inside transaction
$pdo->commit();
```

#### ISSUE-008: Public Upload Directory
```
// ✅ Move /uploads/ outside public webroot
// OR serve via authenticated PHP proxy:
// api/file.php?type=staff_photo&id=123 → validates session → streams file
```

### 11.4 Security Posture Summary

| Threat | Status |
|--------|--------|
| CSRF (all POST endpoints) | ✅ Protected |
| SQL Injection (main flow) | ✅ PDO Prepared Statements |
| SQL Injection (returns filter) | ❌ OPEN |
| Razorpay signature forgery | ✅ hmac_sha256 server-side |
| Razorpay amount mismatch | ✅ Cross-verified |
| OTP brute force | ❌ OPEN |
| Session fixation | ❌ OPEN |
| Blocked user login bypass | ❌ VERIFY |
| File upload type spoofing | ✅ finfo MIME check |
| File upload size abuse | ✅ 5MB limit enforced |
| User data isolation | ✅ All queries include user_id |
| Delivery partner order isolation | ✅ delivery_id check |
| cron.php public access | ❌ OPEN |
| Security HTTP headers | ❌ OPEN |
| Upload directory public | ❌ OPEN |

